summary:
The Security Council,
Reaffirming previous resolutions on the International Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia, 
Having considered the Secretary-General's letters on the election of ad litem judges, 
Noting the need to extend the deadline for nominations and the shortfall in candidates, 
Decides to:
1. Amend article 13 ter of the Statute of the International Tribunal for the Former Yugoslavia;
2. Extend the deadline for nominations of ad litem judges for a further 30 days;
3. Remain seized of the matter.

Annex:
Article 13 ter: 
- Ad litem judges to be elected by the General Assembly from a list submitted by the Security Council;
- Nomination process and requirements;
- Election and appointment procedures;
- Ad litem judges serve for four years, eligible for re-election, and appointed for up to three years.
